  "original_title": "Nestl\u00e9 Lanka recognised Sri Lanka\u2019s Most Respected Food and Beverage Entity in 2022",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nestl\u00e9 Lanka recognised Sri Lanka\u2019s Most Respected Food and Beverage Entity in 2022",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Nestl\u00e9 Lanka was ranked Sri Lanka\u2019s Most Respected Food and Beverage Entity in LMD\u2019s Most Respected Entities issue 2022 released recently.",
        "Accordingly, the company was among the Top 20 Most Respected Entities, out of over 100 renowned corporates across different industries.",
        "\u201cStaying true to our promise of \u2018Good food, Good life\u2019, we have strived to contribute towards healthier families, empowered communities and a greener Sri Lanka for over 115 years. Being declared the \u2018Sector Winner\u2019 in the Food and Beverage category is a reaffirmation of our deep roots in the country and we are honoured to be recognised in such an esteemed ranking.",
        "\u201cAt a time when we are faced with many challenges, this recognition is truly an encouragement for us to continue delivering healthier and tastier products to our beloved Sri Lankan consumers, whilst also continuing our work towards communities and the planet together with our stakeholders across the value chain\u201d, said Nestl\u00e9 Lanka Managing Director Jason Avance\u00f1a.",
        "Being the largest food and beverage company in the world, Nestl\u00e9 has been an integral part of Sri Lankan lives for over 115 years. Driven by its purpose of \u2018unlocking the power of food to enhance quality of life for everyone, today and for generations to come\u2019, Nestl\u00e9 nourishes consumers across generations from early childhood to old age through its diverse food and beverage portfolio.",
        "With over 90% of Nestl\u00e9 products sold in Sri Lanka being manufactured in its state-of-the-art factory in Kurunegala, the company contributes to the socio-economic development of the country. In addition to supporting the livelihoods of over 800 individuals directly employed by the company, being one of the largest exporters of Coconut Milk Powder and one of the largest collectors of fresh milk in Sri Lanka, Nestl\u00e9 Lanka contributes to the local community and support over 25,000 farmers and other business partners across its value chain.",
        "The company is also strongly committed to ensuring its products are good for the planet, by working towards achieving its ambition of net zero emissions across the value chain by 2050.",
        "The LMD \u2018Most Respected\u2019 ranking is based on an annual survey conducted by NielsenIQ, compiling the opinions of survey respondents from over 100 companies. Companies are ranked by respondents across a multitude of parameters, including quality consciousness, innovation, CSR, corporate culture, dynamism, honesty, management profile and vision."
      ],
